audit of audit-messy

errors:
  ✗ [junk-files] `.env` is committed (looks like an environment/secrets file)
    fix: run `git rm --cached .env`, add it to .gitignore, and rotate the secret if the repo was ever pushed
  ✗ [readme] the repo has no README
    fix: add one, for example with `hpds use readme`
  ✗ [lifecycle-metadata] hpds.toml does not set `project.primary-author`
    fix: add `primary-author = "<github-username>"` under [project] in hpds.toml
  ✗ [lockfiles] the project uses renv but renv.lock is not committed
    fix: run `renv::snapshot()` in R, then commit renv.lock

warnings:
  ! [dirty-files] 1 tracked file has uncommitted changes (analysis.R)
    fix: commit the changes (`git add` / `git commit`) or stash them (`git stash`)
  ! [stale-artifacts] `report.html` is older than its source `report.qmd`
    fix: re-render it (`quarto render report.qmd`) and commit the result
  ! [junk-files] `.DS_Store` is committed (macOS Finder junk)
    fix: run `git rm --cached .DS_Store` and ignore it (`hpds git vaccinate --project` adds the common patterns)
  ! [gitignore-hygiene] .gitignore is missing the recommended R patterns: .Rhistory, .RData, .Rproj.user, .Rdata, .httr-oauth, .DS_Store
    fix: run `hpds git vaccinate --project` to add them

info:
  • [untracked-files] 1 file is neither tracked nor ignored (scratch-notes.txt)
    fix: commit each file, add it to .gitignore, or delete it
  • [stale-branches] local branch `old-work` is fully merged
    fix: delete it with `git branch -d old-work`
  • [github] GitHub checks skipped: no origin remote
    fix: if this project should live on GitHub, create the repo (`hpds repo create`) or point origin at it (`git remote add origin <url>`); purely local repos can ignore this

4 errors, 4 warnings, 3 info across 9 checks
